Oba Olalekan James, the Aholu of Kweme Kingdom, Badagry, Lagos State, has vowed to make cultism a thing of the past in his kingdom. The royal father made the promise at a stakeholders’ meeting in his palace in Badagry West Local Council Development Area (LCDA) on Tuesday. Julius Berger grows revenue by 40% Gombe gov warns residents against building on waterways According to the monarch, the activities of cult members have taken a dangerous turn, hence that all hands must be on deck to stop them from perpetrating their evil acts. He said, “Every cultist is a potential armed robber or hired assassin. Henceforth, any cult activity perpetrated within the kingdom will not be treated with kid gloves no matter whose ox is gored.”